						        Q:
								


"I have my 82 year old mother that has accidents during the night.  Would this pad absorb the urine and keep the mattress dry?"








									Enter your answer
								









Follow



    									Submit
    								

    									Cancel
    								
By clicking submit, you accept our Terms & Conditions







									    A:
										


Can't give you a definitive answer as the mattress cover was my third line of defense for my mom with similar issues. It was for in case her overnight depends, rubber pants and quilted bed pads failed which was never the case. I think it is a good product and definitely protects the mattress from some spills and leaks but not sure if there is a large volume if it will do all you need it to do. If you are having these issues, I would recommend starting to use other protective products made for incontinence in addition to using the mattress cover as a safeguard. It is a pain to have to strip and wash bedding every day. Much better to get the appropriate products easily available through the mail . Good luck.

Beth S.
May 9, 2017





 






